The Pho, Banh Mi, even something more specific like Bun Bo Hue or Banh Xeo (Vietnamese Pancake) are all tasty and quite authentic. The Pho broth was full of aroma and deliciously well. Not all of the  Vietnamese sandwiches were good, but the Cold Cut, 3 Layer Pork, BBQ Pork, and Special were irresistibly mouthwatering. They even have the avocado smoothie made from real avocado with boba to wash down the protein. The service was pleasant, but the price of the food makes this restaurant a bang for my buck and become my new favorite restaurant. Otherwise, the rice platter was under average as the grilled meat and pork chop, and even the fish sauce was undercooked, unauthentic, and lack of flavor when I had it.
